values.description:
@sherm1 pointed out in pull request #82 that identifiers shouldn't start with an underscore followed by a capital letter (`_[A-Z]`). This includes functions and header guards. So I wrote cppcheck rules for both of these cases ([failure confirmed here](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/ignition_math-ci-pr_any-trusty-amd64/67/cppcheckResult/)) and fixed them as necessary.

In d305336, I added `IGN_SQRT2` so `_USE_MATH_DEFINES` isn't necessary.

I also fixed the header guards as necessary.

